<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre>Crypt files via key pair

Create the key pair
    gpg --gen-key

Listing:
  List your key in simple format
    gpg --list-keys

  List private key
    gpg --list-secret-keys

  List your key in long format
    gpg --list-keys --keyid-format long

  List private key in long format
    gpg --list-secret-keys --keyid-format long

Export:
  Export public key ASCII format
    gpg --armor --output MyKeyPub.asc --export &quot;user_name&quot;

  Export private key
     gpg --export-secret-key -a &gt; MyPrivateKey.key

Import:
  Import a key
    gpg --import --allow-secret-key-import MaPrivateKey.key

Link:
  Manuel Gnupg
    http://www.gnupg.org/gph/en/manual.html

  Manuel Gnupg in a french
    http://www.gnupg.org/gph/fr/manual.html
